{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# How to select a mesh subset?\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows how to select a subset of a mesh that is encoded by a color."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[KeOps] Warning : cuda was detected, but driver API could not be initialized. Switching to cpu only.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pyvista as pv\n",
    "\n",
    "import polpo.preprocessing.dict as ppdict\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.load.pregnancy.pilot import (\n",
    "    HippocampalSubfieldsSegmentationsLoader,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.conversion import PvFromData\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.filter import PvSelectColor\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mri import (\n",
    "    MeshExtractorFromSegmentedImage,\n",
    "    segmtool2encoding,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "STATIC_VIZ = True\n",
    "\n",
    "if STATIC_VIZ:\n",
    "    pv.set_jupyter_backend(\"static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Mesh from MRI"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Following [How to get a mesh from an MRI image?](mri2mesh.ipynb), we get a `pv.PolyData` object representing the hippocampus."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "SESSION_ID = 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipe = (\n",
    "    HippocampalSubfieldsSegmentationsLoader(subset=[SESSION_ID], as_image=True)\n",
    "    + ppdict.ExtractUniqueKey()\n",
    "    + MeshExtractorFromSegmentedImage(encoding=\"ashs\")\n",
    "    + PvFromData()\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "INFO: Data has already been downloaded... using cached file ('/home/luisfpereira/.herbrain/data/pregnancy/derivatives/segmentations').\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mesh = pipe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pl = pv.Plotter(border=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.show_axes()\n",
    "pl.add_mesh(mesh, show_edges=True)\n",
    "pl.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Select a substructure"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Substructures are encoded by colors. In this particular case, the encoding is generated by [ASHS](https://www.nitrc.org/projects/ashs). We provide access to the encoding."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "encoding = segmtool2encoding(tool=\"ashs\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We now create a preprocessing step that selects the cells of the mesh with the given color."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "struct_selector = PvSelectColor(extract_surface=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_cols = 3\n",
    "pl = pv.Plotter(shape=(3, n_cols), border=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "for index, (struct_name, color) in enumerate(encoding.structs2colors.items()):\n",
    "    row, col = index // n_cols, index % n_cols\n",
    "    pl.subplot(row, col)\n",
    "\n",
    "    substructure = struct_selector((mesh, color))\n",
    "\n",
    "    pl.show_axes()\n",
    "    substructure.clear_data()\n",
    "    pl.add_mesh(substructure, show_edges=True)\n",
    "    pl.add_title(struct_name, font_size=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Any mesh preprocessing step can now be applied to the substructure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "NB: recall that a substructure can directly be extracted from the image, as shown [here](./mri2mesh.ipynb)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# TODO: show that doing extraction in the image leads to different results"
   ]
  }
